¢Plan for and respond to a disaster or bioterrorism event in our community: work with other agencies and health care and emergency response professionals to plan for a unified response to disaster.\nâ¢Protect the Environment: inspect and license all food services, private sewage systems and private water sources. \nâ¢Provide Clinical Preventive Services: immunizations and screenings are provided with a focus on individuals underserved by the private system.\nâ¢Provide prevention education to help individuals stay healthy.\nâ¢Assist targeted high risk groups in seeking medical and social services.\n \nThe Hamilton County Health Department is working to improve health and safety in Hamilton County.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPlease click on the box below to print a copy of the Covid-19 Consent form for HCHD.  Please fill out the yellow highlighted sections and bring said completed form with you once you are eligible to receive the vaccine at one of our scheduled drive-thru clinics.  Phase restrictions will be posted on our website, along with our Facebook page and on local media outlets for your convenience.  If you have any insurance coverage, please have your insurance card (s) with you, along with ID and/or proof of employment if needed for proof of eligibility at the time of vaccination.  Please Note:  You will not  be charged or receive a bill for the allowed billable vaccination administration amount regardless if you have insurance or not.  The vaccine itself is free of charge.\n\n\n\n\nClick below to review a copy of the Emergency Use Authorizations for the current approved Covid-19 Vaccines:\n\n\n\n\n\n\n          Pfizer EUA for Vaccine Recipients \n        \n\n\n\n\n\n\n          Moderna Vaccine EUA for Recipients \n        \n\n\n\n\n\n\nCurrent Covid-19 Vaccination Phase for Hamilton County per IDPH:\n  PHASE - 1b \n Please see below for drive-thru clinic dates & times, location, restrictions, forms and additional information.\nClick below for the link to the