NOTE: If you are NOT in the Phase 1B or the Phase 1C priority group and complete the Phase 1B and Phase 1C Enrollment Form, your submission will be invalidated and you will need to resubmit a vaccine enrollment form for your group. \n                 \nPlease complete the enrollment form below regarding you or your organizations interest in receiving the COVID-19 vaccine. The enrollment form is not a registration form for an appointment to receive the vaccine. A separate link will be sent to the e-mail you provide when completing the enrollment form and will include information on how to register for an appointment once clinics become available. \nThe enrollment form will be used to determine the amount of vaccine we will be allocating to different priority groups at this time. If you are completing the enrollment on behalf of an organization, please include the organizations name, primary contact information and the number of staff who want the vaccine. The link for your organization to register for appointments will be sent to the primary contact e-mail to be forwarded to your employees. \nIf you are a healthcare provider, please do not use this form. Healthcare providers should use the Healthcare Provider Enrollment form instead.\n\n\nPhase 1B And 1C Vaccine Enrollment Form\n\n\nFormulario de inscripción de la vacunación para la Fase 1B y la Fase 1C\n\n\n\nList of Phase 1B Job Titles/Positions\n\n\n\n\r\nVaccine Enrollment - Phase 1A\nNOTE: If you are NOT in the Phase 1A priority group and complete the Healthcare Provider Enrollment Form, your submission will be invalidated and you will need to resubmit a vaccine enrollment form for your group.  \n\nAt this time, we are asking for vaccination interest for staff who provide direct patient care and are certified/licensed healthcare professionals. These staff should either provide care in or be residents of McHenry County. \nPlease complete the enrollment form linked below regarding those eligible staff who intend on receiving the vaccine. For practices/organizations providing care in McHenry County, we ask that a main point of contact for the practice/organization complete this form for all staff interested in the vaccine. This helps ensure duplicate responses are not submitted by multiple staff members.\nThis is not a registration form for an appointment to receive the vaccine. A separate link will be used to register for appointment times once they become available. This form will be used to determine the amount of vaccine we will be allocating to different priority groups at this time.\n\n\nHealthcare Provider Enrollment\n\n\nList of Phase 1A Job Titles/Positions \n\n\nFrequently Asked Questions:\nInformation is constantly becoming available and changing. Please check back regularly to get the latest information about COVID-19 vaccines. \n\n\nCOVID-19 FAQ \n\n\n\r\nOther Resources:\nThe Illinois Department of Public Health (IDPH) publishes data about the number of vaccinated individuals by their county of residence and the amount of vaccine distributed to each county. This data does not immediately reflect the number of doses administered at MCDH vaccine clinics. For more information about how vaccine administered data is collected, please read the \"Data Definitions\" section on IDPHs Vaccine Administration Data page. Additional information about the States vaccine distribution plan that MCDH is using to help guide its distribution process is also available on IDPHs website. \n\n\nIDPH Vaccine Administration Data for McHenry County\n\n\nState of Illinois COVID-19 Vaccination Plan\n\n\n\n\n\r\nE-notification Sign-Ups \nWe will be using an electronic registration format to ensure we are providing vaccines as safe as possible, but it will not be open to the general public until we complete the vaccination of all those on the priority list. \nThe best way to be notified of when our electronic registration form will be open to your priority group or the general public is to sign up for e-notifications. Any news release we share or event we post to the website will be delivered directly to your email. \nTo sign up, complete the form below and click the envelope icons next to Health Department Events and Health Department Press Releases.\nYou will be sent a verification email after you register (check your junk and spam inboxes). You  must verify your email to complete your e-notification subscription. \n\nSign Up for MCDH eNotifications\n\n\neNotification Signup | Change eNotification Preferences\n\n\n\n\n\nPlease correct the fields below:\n\n\n\nEmail Address *\n\n\n\nRetype Email Address *\n\n\n\nFirst Name *\n\n\n\nLast Name *\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCalendar\n\n\nHealth Department Events\nEmail Notification\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nNews\n\n\nHealth Department Press Releases\nEmail Notification\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSubscribe to All Emails\nSubscribe to All Emails\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nTo prevent spam we utilize a verification code system. Please enter the code as it is shown in the box below:\n\n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCode:','No content','60098','2200 N SEMINARY AVE, #B WOODSTOCK 60098',1,NULL,'2021-02-27 10:30:50','2021-02-27 10:30:50','MCHENRY COUNTY DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH','IL','div|standardlayout clearfix'),(252,12,'https://health.mcleancountyil.gov/791/Vaccination-Clinics','No content','No content','61701','200 W FRONT ST, SUITE 304 BLOOMINGTON 61701',1,NULL,'2021-02-27 10:32:07','2021-02-27 10:32:07','MCLEAN COUNTY DEPARTMENT OF PUBLIC HEALTH','IL','div|structuralContainer7'),(253,12,'https://clinic.meijer.com/','No content','No content','60440','225 N Weber Road Boilingbrook 60440',1,NULL,'2021-02-27 10:33:01','2021-02-27 10:33:01','MEIJER PHARMACY','IL','PHARMACY'),(254,12,'https://events.juvare.com/IL-IDPH/ba7ef27c-8cbf-49aa-a678-c83e03f056b7/','No content','No content','62226','4700 Memorial Dr. (3rd Floor Neuroscience Center) Belleville 62226',1,NULL,'2021-02-27 10:34:23','2021-02-27 10:34:23','Memorial Hospital','IL','div|container main-box'),(255,12,'https://monroecountyhealth.org/home/emergency-preparedness/covid-19/covid-19-vaccine-information/','COVID-19 Vaccine has arrived in Monroe County\nPlease follow our Facebook page, this website or register with Code RED for clinic announcements. Please complete the consent form and bring with you to the clinic. Listed below is the vaccine fact sheet that will be provided to you when you receive the vaccine. V-safe is an app you may utilize after receiving the vaccine to report any and all side effects you may experience.\n\nCOVID-19 Vaccine Consent Form\nCOVID-19 Moderna Vaccine Fact Sheet\nCOVID-19 Pfizer Vaccine Fact Sheet\nv-safe (after vaccination health checker)\nRegister for Code RED\n\n**Next COVID-19 Vaccine (Moderna 2nd dose) Clinic: \nONLY FOR INDIVIDUALS THAT RECEIVED THEIR 1st DOSE ON JANUARY 18th\n \nMonday, February 22, 2021\n10:00 am until 3pm (or until all 2nd doses have been administered)\nMonroe County Fairgrounds\n \n2nd doses for individuals that received their 1st dose on January 18th\n*Bring proof of identity and vaccination card from 1st clinic\n*Bring completed COVID-19 Vaccine Consent Form (available at gate as well)\n \n**Next COVID-19 Vaccine (Moderna 2nd dose) Clinic: \nONLY FOR INDIVIDUALS THAT RECEIVED THEIR 1st DOSE ON JANUARY 27th & 28th\n \nThursday, February 25, 2021\n10:00 am until 2pm (or until all 2nd doses have been administered)\nMonroe County Fairgrounds\n \n2nd doses for individuals that received their 1st dose on January 27th & 28th\n*Bring proof of identity and vaccination card from 1st clinic\n*Bring completed COVID-19 Vaccine Consent Form (available at gate as well)\n \n**Do NOT call the health department for your second vaccine. You must wait a minimum of 21 days with the Pfizer & 28 days with Moderna vaccine before your second dose. Your second dose may not be administered exactly 21 days or 28 days later due to variable shipment dates. You will receive your 2nd dose within the allotted time.\n\nDO NOT ARRIVE PRIOR TO 10am. Gates will NOT be open.\nNo pre-registration needed.\nCovid-19 consent form needs to be completed prior to arrival if possible. We will have some available at the gate upon arrival.\nPlease NOTE: Individuals receiving their 2nd dose from another 1st dose clinic will need to wait! We will be receiving a special shipment for you this week.\n\nDO NOT CALL THE MONROE COUNTY SHERIFF’S OFFICE FOR COVID RELATED QUESTIONS OR CONCERNS!','No content','62298','1315 JAMIE LN WATERLOO 62298',1,NULL,'2021-02-27 10:35:20','2021-02-27 10:35:20','MONROE COUNTY HEALTH DEPARTMENT','IL','div|site-content'),(256,12,'https://www.morganhd.com/covid-19/covid-19-vaccine','COVID-19 VaccinePre-Registration now open to morgan county residents 65 years of age or olderAge eligible adults may pre-register by calling:217-479-1817**Please do not leave a message at this number. Due to the high volume of calls, staff will not be able to return messages in a timely manner.Pre-Registered Seniors will receive a call from \"Morgan County COVID Response\" staff with the date, time and location of your first dose.Call Center Staff available: 9 AM to 4 PM, Monday - Friday (closed on all Federal, State and locally observed holidays)Businesses that meet the criteria for 1a or 1b vaccine eligibility will be contacted directly by the Morgan County Mass Vaccination Planning Team to coordinate this service for your staff. For a list of other COVID Vaccine Providers and Locations visit the IDPH Vaccination Location SiteThe US Food & Drug Administration has granted Emergency Use Authorizations for COVID-19 vaccines from the following manufacturers:PfizerModernaFor more information visit the CDC Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) PageTo sign up for alerts or report an adverse event following vaccination for COVID-19 visit vsafe.cdc.govIDPH: Illinois Department of Public HealthCDC: Centers for Disease Control and PreventionACIP: Advisory Committee on Immunization PracticesFDA: U.S. Food & Drug Administration','No content','62650','345 W STATE ST JACKSONVILLE 62650',1,NULL,'2021-02-27 10:37:14','2021-02-27 10:37:14','MORGAN COUNTY HEALTH DEPARTMENT','IL','div|UtePc RCETm'),(257,12,'https://morrisonhospital.com/','COVID TESTING AND VACCINE UPDATE\n\n\n\n\nCOVID TESTING\n If you are exhibiting symptoms of fever, cough, sore throat, shortness of breath, diarrhea, vomiting, loss of smell or taste, and/or headache please call 815-772-5511    A receptionist will schedule an appointment and you will then be transferred to a medical provider for screening.\n COVID VACCINES\nTo all of our valued patients and Whiteside County residents over the age of 65, we are taking names of individuals in the Phase 1b category to be scheduled for their vaccine.  Until vaccine supplies increase, and more of Phase 1B has been completed, we will not begin vaccinating Phase 1b+.  Please call 815-772-5537 to have your name added to our list.\nThank you for choosing Morrison Community Hospital\n \n \nLearn More\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFamily Care Clinic\nOur Walk-in Family Practice Providers treat patients with common colds to more serious ailments such as lacerations, infections and other ailments. Tele-Psychiatry, Dermatology, Cardiology, and Gastroenterology services are now being provided in the Family Care Clinic. Hours: 8:00 AM – 6:00 PM Seven days a week.  815-772-5511\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSpecialty Clinic Services\nDr. Priyanka Gauravi, Endocrinologist, treats patients with diabetes and patients with thyroid disorders in the Specialty Clinic. Dr. Thane Cody, Otolaryngologist, treats ear, nose and throat maladies for patients from infants to adults. Please call 815-772-5590 to find our more information or to schedule an appointment.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nRehabilitation Services\nPhysical, occupational, and speech rehab is offered at Morrison Hospital. We also provide Massage Therapy. Call 815-772-5548 to schedule an appointment or get more information.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMedical / Surgical Services\nThe Morrison Community Hospital Medical and Surgical Department cares for a wide variety of patients from pediatric to geriatric with various medical conditions. We provide Acute Care, Skilled Care, Wound Care, Outpatient IV therapies and Hospice Care.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nLaboratory\nWe provide in-patient and out-patient services for the procurement of blood, urine and other specimens, and the testing of these specimens is performed with state of the art laboratory instrumentation. The lab provides tests 24 hours per day, 365 days per year. Call 815-772-5536 to make an appointment.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nRadiology\nThe Radiology department offers both screening and diagnostic tests to both inpatients and outpatients.  We offer many imaging procedures including; general x-rays, CT, MRI, bone density testing, and diagnostic ultrasound. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFoundation Events\nThe mission of the Morrison Community Hospital Foundation is to support the Morrison Community Hospital, foster its growth, and to perpetuate excellence in healthcare. For more information on our special events or to partner with us financially please click on the Foundation tab.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nBilling / Insurance / Patient Records\nA list of insurance plans accepted by Morrison Community Hospital is available by clicking on the “About Us” tab and then scroll down to “Insurance”. To request patient records call 815-772-5527. To pay a bill or get answers to questions on a billing statement call 815-772-5517.  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nVoter Referendum\n\nATTENTION VOTERS:\r\nOn behalf of the patients and staff at the Morrison Community Hospital we want to thank you for approving our referendum. As noted this will NOT increase your taxes. This agreement allows our doctors to see patients in offices outside of our hospital district. Dr. Foad currently sees patients each Thursday in his Davenport office. That office is located at 4322 Progress Drive, Suite C, Davenport IA. All surgeries for those patients will be performed at the Morrison Community Hospital.\n\nLearn More\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPre-Grand Opening- Saturday, April 10\n\nSATURDAY, APRIL 10, 9:00 AM\r\nODELL LIBRARY COMMUNITY ROOM\r\n307 S. Madison Street\r\nMorrison, IL 61270\r\n\r\nDoors open at 8:30 AM\r\nBreakfast will be served\r\n9:00- Video and photo presentation of the hospital expansion progress\r\n9:20- Dr. Foad, Yeager and Olney will introduce themselves and talk about how the expansion will help them treat patients\r\n9:40- Morrison Resident Joe Mills, Financial Advisor, will talk about unique ways to financially support the hospital expansion\r\n\r\nSeating is limited. Please call Mick at 815-772-5510 to reserve a spot or email Mick at mwelding@mchstaff.com and let him know how many seats you would like.\r\n\n\nLearn More\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nGala Video\n\nClick below to view the Morrison Community Hospital 2020 Gala Video\n\nLearn More\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSilent Auction\n\nThank you for purchasing silent auction items and raffle items. Revenues from the silent auction items totaled $6,928. The raffle items brought in another $2,085. The winners of the (2) 1/4 beef packages were Kathy Windover and Randy Foster. Kelly Vegter was the winner of the $1.000 cash and she graciously donated it back to the foundation. Total revenues from the auction, raffle and donations totaled $12,263.\n\nView Silent Auction Items\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nDonations\n\nThank you for considering a donation to the Morrison Community Hospital Foundation. To discover ways to participate please call 815-772-5510.\n\nLearn More\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nFoundation Events\n\nThe Morrison Community Hospital Foundation Board of Directors is constantly looking at creative ways to foster fellowship and in turn, raise funds for a project at the hospital.\n\nLearn More\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nGallery Page\n\nView our gallery.\n\nLearn More\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nMemorials and Dedications\n\n