s in a timely manner, however, if you need immediate assistance, please call 1-800-252-1818 during regular business hours (Monday through Friday, 8 a.m. - 5 p.m.), excluding state holidays. We look forward to assisting you.\nPlease disable your pop-up blocker if you do not see a contact form to complete below.\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPage last updated: February 22, 2021','No content','36854','-',1,NULL,'2021-02-27 14:04:04','2021-02-27 14:04:04','Chambers County Health Department - Valley','AL','div|row mainContent'),(305,10,'https://www.hilomedicalcenter.org/covid-19-vaccine-sign-up-information/','COVID-19 Vaccination Application\n\n\nClick on the link to view the instructional video to schedule your appointment on VAMS: https://youtu.be/rLKAVNfSNDo.\nIf you qualify for any of the below groups, please fill out the appropriate form. You must bring your identification and insurance card to your appointment. For essential workers a work ID/work paystub will also be required.\n\nUpon completion of the below forms, your information will be submitted to the CDC. You will receive an email from the CDC within two business days to register for the VAMS website. Please watch this instructional video to learn how to register and schedule your appointment on the VAMS website by clicking here.\n\nAfter creating your VAMS account, you can schedule an appointment at any available vaccine distribution site on Hawaii Island. The VAMS user manual can be found by clicking here.\nEach recipient MUST have an individual email address to sign up, you cannot have the same email address as any other vaccine recipient, it must be unique to you.\n\n\n\n\nPlease Be Aware of Hilo Medical Centers Vaccine Availability\n\n\n\nHilo Medical Center is focused on specializing in vaccinating our kupuna.\nWe are currently vaccinating our kupuna 75 years and older.\n65+ can complete the 1st step of the registration process on HiloMedicalCenter.org. Pre-registering on our site will hold your place in line to receive an email from the CDC  to register for your shot.\nIn order to ensure vaccines are available for you, we only open appointment slots as vaccines become available. Currently all vaccine supplies are being utilized by our 75+ population. Until we receive additional vaccines, we will not be vaccinating 65+ and other groups until further notice.\nVaccination appointments for 65+ will be made available as vaccines are received.\nPlease refrain from calling the helpline if you are not 75 and older to allow access for our very senior and most vulnerable population.\nOur commitment is to give out the vaccines we receive – currently a 1,000  plus doses per week.\nPlease continue to visit us at www.HiloMedicalCenter.org for the latest information about our vaccination clinic.\n\n\n\nMedical Professionals\nGroup 1A\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nEssential Workers\n\nClick Here\n\n\n\n\nEssential WorkersGroup 1A Click Here\n75 and Over\nGroup 1B\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n75 Years or Older\n\nClick Here\n\n\n\n\n75 and OverGroup 1B Click Here\n\n\nNon-Medical Essential Workers\nGroup 1B - Start date TBD*\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nNon-Medical Essential Workers\n\nClick Here\n\n\n\n\nEssential WorkersGroup 1B Click Here – Start Date TBD*\n*Subject to Vaccine Availability\n65 to 74 Years Old\nGroup 1C - Start Date TBD*\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n65 to 74 Years Old\n\nClick Here\n\n\n\n\n65 to 74 Years OldGroup 1C Click Here – Start Date TBD*\n*Subject to Vaccine Availability','No content','96720','-',1,NULL,'2021-02-27 14:05:05','2021-02-27 14:05:05','Hilo Medical Center','HI','div|wpb_column vc_main_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12 typo-default'),(306,67,'https://www.mainstreetfamilycare.com/locations/valley/','No content','No content','36854','-',1,NULL,'2021-02-27 14:06:17','2021-02-27 14:06:17','Mainstreet Family Care - Valley','AL','div|inner-content'),(307,67,'https://www.mainstreetfamilycare.com/locations/centre/','No content','No content','30188','-',1,NULL,'2021-02-27 14:08:42','2021-02-27 14:08:42','Main