ollowing conditions are eligible for Bio Monitoring Case Management:\n\nDiabetes\nHypertension\nCongestive Heart Failure\n\nDepending on your diagnosis, you could receive free monitoring equipment such as a glucometer, blood pressure monitor and/or a set of weight monitoring scales. A Registered Nurse will work with you and your doctor to achieve improved outcomes for your chronic disease. If you would like to participate in the program at no cost to you, or you would like information about this program, contact Margaret Ezell at (334) 358-2002 or 1-888-749-5694.\nHome Health Services\nHome Health services are available for residents of Autauga, Chilton, Elmore, Lee, Macon and Montgomery counties. Visit Home Care for more information.\nCustomer Satisfaction Survey\nThe Alabama Department of Public Health is asking patients of our county health departments to complete a customer satisfaction survey. ADPH cares about what you think of the services we provide. We value your feedback and look forward to receiving your ratings and comments.\n\nCustomer Satisfaction Survey (English)\nCustomer Satisfaction Survey (Spanish)\n\n\n\n\n\nPage last updated: February 25, 2021','No content','35045','-',1,NULL,'2021-02-27 14:10:20','2021-02-27 14:10:20','Chilton County Health Department','AL','div|row mainContent'),(309,10,'https://kch.hhsc.org/covid-19-hospital-preparedness-message/','COVID-19 Community Updates and Information \n\nUpdated 2/16/2021                                                                                                                 \nTo our Community:\nThis page is devoted to keeping our community updated with current news and information about the COVID-19 pandemic. We will also provide information regarding the COVID-19 vaccine as it becomes available.\nKCH Community COVID-19 Update for Feb. 16, 2021 (click here)\nHospital Visitor Restrictions Remain in Effect (click here)\nKCH Vaccine Clinic:\nKCH is a registered clinic in the CDC Vaccination Provider Program. With this honor comes responsibilities and guidelines to be followed by our organization. We’re committed to operating the KCH vaccine clinic in accordance with our CDC Vaccination Provider Program Agreement, and in cooperation with the Hawaii Department of Health. This is huge undertaking, and the team is working tirelessly to manage all facets of launching and operating a large-scale vaccine clinic.\nWe are vaccinating:\n\nPhase 1A  eligible healthcare workers and active community healthcare workers\nPhase 1B individuals who are 75+ years of age.\n\nDue to very high volume in this age range, we are not yet vaccinating Tier 1B essential workers or individuals below 75 years of age.\n\n\n\nKupuna Vaccine Clinic Details Flyer (click for details)\nKupuna Clinic Registration Form (click image below)\nWho is eligible? Tier 1A – frontline and community healthcare workers. Tier 1B – Kupuna, individuals 75 years of age and up. We are NOT yet vaccinating other essential workers or people below the age of 75.\n___________________________________________________________________________\nClick image to view Kupuna clinic info for Hawaii County.\n______________________________________________________________________\n\n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n\n\n \nClick here to learn about COVID-19 Vaccine from Hawaii DOH\nCommunity Testing Sites – Hawaii Island Pages 7-9 (updated 1/19/2020)\n**Note: Beginning Jan. 1, 2021, patients may incur a co-pay or lab bill at community testing sites.\n\nWe encourage you to look for the most current information:\n\nCenters for Disease Control and Prevention:  coronavirus.gov\nState of Hawaii Dept. of Health (includes Frequently Asked Questions in languages other than English)\nState of Hawaii Dept. of Health – Printable materials, including foreign languages.\nState of Hawaii Dedicated COVID website  www.HawaiiCOVID19.com\nRegister for State of Hawaii Dept. of Health daily email updates','No content','96750','-',1,NULL,'2021-02-27 14:10:38','202