ly is limited.','02451','860 Winter St, Waltham, MA 02451, United States',1,NULL,'2021-02-28 13:54:43','2021-02-28 13:54:43','Massachusetts Medical Society','MA','div|structColumnMain'),(516,31,'https://www.chnnyc.org/for-patients/covid19-vaccine/','No content','The COVID-19 pandemic has been a stressful time for many of us, causing many changes in our everyday lives. The good news is there is now a vaccine (shot) that can help protect you and others from getting COVID-19. It is perfectly normal if you have some questions about this new vaccine, and we are here to help answer them! Use these FAQs to learn more about this vaccine and how it works. Talk with your CHN doctor if you have questions or concerns.\n \n\nPlease note: We are unable to schedule vaccine appointments as we are waiting for more doses. Please check back for updates.','11435','9704 Sutphin Blvd, Jamaica, NY',1,NULL,'2021-02-28 14:01:24','2021-02-28 14:10:14','CHN Community Health Network','NY','div|content content_top_margin'),(517,20,'https://www.capecodhealth.org/medical-services/infectious-disease/coronavirus/','No content','Cape Cod Healthcare is administering vaccines to our highest risk eligible residents across Cape Cod. Currently this is accomplished by our team directly calling patients that have been previously identified by the consortium or within our health system records. We cannot receive incoming calls for vaccine scheduling. We are working with Barnstable County to request access to the state scheduling system called PrepMod. Once available, a number of appointments will be made available to the public for self-registration. Thank you for your patience; we are very proud and excited to be a part of vaccinating so many residents across Cape Cod.','02601','27 Park St, Hyannis, MA 02601, United States',1,NULL,'2021-02-28 14:15:20','2021-02-28 14:16:40','CAPE COD HEALTHCARE','MA','div|cmsPageContent'),(518,20,'https://vaxfinder.mass.gov/locations/fenway-park/','No content','Use this pa